dba sql Function experiment               
========================================================================
$Id$

==========================
extends class generator
extends experiment dbConstraints
extends experiment dbProjection
extends experiment dbProxy

==========================
Use Sql-Functions in criteria.
Function expressinons can be used in the restriction part an in the
projectiopn pasr of the SQL query.

example for the restriction part:
$crits[]= Criteria::newInstance()->add(Restrictions::equal(SQLFunctions::month("registration_date"), "05");

example for the projection part:
$crits[]= Criteria::newInstance()->setProjection(
  Projections::Property(
    SQLFunctions::dateadd('day', '-4', SQLFunctions::getdate())
  ),
  'datediffTest'
);

example for nested functions:
$crits[]= Criteria::newInstance()->setProjection(
  Projections::Property(
    SQLFunctions::datename('hour', SQLFunctions::getdate()),
    'datenameTest'
  )
);


<EOF>
